{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015qvWeE8utemDccnDJdCQtT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three verification conditions pass:\n\n1. **Cluster health: green** — `status: green`, 3/3 data nodes, 0 unassigned shards\n2. **All nodes present** — `es-cluster-0`, `es-cluster-1`, and `es-cluster-2` all appear in `/_cat/nodes`\n3. **app-data readable** — index search returns the seed document successfully\n\n**Root cause:** The `es-config` ConfigMap had two injected faults:\n- `node.name: ` (null value) — caused Elasticsearch to crash immediately on startup before forming any connection\n- `discovery.seed_hosts` pointed to `.default.svc.cluster.local` instead of `.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` — would have prevented cluster discovery even if the node started\n\n**Fix:** Patched the ConfigMap to remove the null `node.name` line (Elasticsearch defaults to the pod hostname, which matches `cluster.initial_master_nodes`) and corrected the seed host namespace, then deleted the failed pod to let the StatefulSet restart it with the corrected config."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":785,"cache_read_input_tokens":38227,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":785},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"73410223-d6e4-410e-933f-1b516cc62ad0","uuid":"4386b6b8-da2f-4618-8401-6e2e0ae16234","request_id":"req_011Cc53ZQF6MzCD9kcSFndK2"}
